claim.claim-text:
15. A method of designing a transformer comprising: determining a set of parameters associated with a conventional transformer having a primary and a secondary coil, the set of parameters of at least one coil of the primary and secondary coils including a specified diameter of the coil and a specified width of a conductor that forms the coil, and
defining a layout of each of the primary and secondary coils that includes a layout of a plurality of N coil segments connected in parallel for each of the primary and secondary coils, the plurality of N coil segments for each of the primary and secondary coils being interleaved and forming loops on a common plane surface having a diameter that is substantially equal to the specified diameter;
wherein the plurality of N coil segments of the at least one coil are each formed using conductors having a width that is substantially equal to the specified width divided by N.
